ic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/136705/', '[1] "Product Information. Valcyte (valganciclovir)" Roche Laboratories, Nutley, NJ.[2] Cerner Multum, Inc. "Australian Product Information." O 0[3] Cerner Multum, Inc. "UK Summary of Product Characteristics." O 0[4] "Product Information. Cytovene (ganciclovir)." Genentech, South San Francisco, CA.[5] "Product Information. Cytovene (ganciclovir)." Genentech, South San Francisco, CA.[6] Jung D, Griffy K, Dorr A "Effect of food on high-dose oral ganciclovir disposition in HIV-positive subjects." J Clin Pharmacol 39 (1999): 161-5[7] Lavelle J, Follansbee S, Trapnell CB, Buhles WC, Griffy KG, Jung D, Dorr A, Conner J "Effect of food on the relative bioavailability of oral ganciclovir." J Clin Pharmacol 36 (1996): 238-41', 1767369485);
