mfetol, Caffeine, Methylphenidate, Dexmethylphenidate, Armodafinil, Citicoline', 'Moderate', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/137103/', '[1] Mugele J, Nanagas KA, Tormoehlen LM "Serotonin Syndrome Associated With MDPV Use: A Case Report." Ann Emerg Med (2012):[2] Gillman PK "Monoamine oxidase inhibitors, opioid analgesics and serotonin toxicity." Br J Anaesth (2005):[3] "Product Information. Sanorex (mazindol)" Novartis Pharmaceuticals, East Hanover, NJ.[4] "Product Information. Desoxyn (methamphetamine)" Abbott Pharmaceutical, Abbott Park, IL.[5] "Product Information. Nuedexta (dextromethorphan-quinidine)." Avanir Pharmaceuticals, Inc, Aliso Viejo, CA.[6] "Product Information. Adipex-P (phentermine)." Teva Pharmaceuticals (formerly Gate Pharmaceuticals), Sellersville, PA.[7] "Product Information. Adderall (amphetamine-dextroamphetamine)" Shire Richwood Pharmaceutical Company, Florence, KY.[8] Davis JJ, Buck NS, Swenson JD, Johnson KB, Greis PE "Serotonin syndrome manifesting as patient movement during total intravenous anesthesia with propofol and remifentanil." J Clin Anesth 25 (2013): 52-4[9] "Product Information. Vyvanse (lisdexamfetamine)." Shire US Inc, Florence, KY.[10] Lee J, Franz L, Goforth HW "Serotonin syndrome in a chronic-pain patient receiving concurrent methadone, ciprofloxacin, and venlafaxine." Psychosomatics 50 (2009): 638-9[11] Hunter B, Kleinert MM, Osatnik J, Soria E "Serotonergic syndrome and abnormal ocular movements: worsening of rigidity by remifentanil?" Anesth Analg 102 (2006): 1589[12] Mendelson J, Jones RT, Upton R, Jacob P 3rd "Methamphetamine and ethanol interactions in humans." Clin Pharmacol Ther 57 (1995): 559-68[13] "Product Information. Didrex (benzphetamine)" Pharmacia and Upjohn, Kalamazoo, MI.[14] "Product Information. Suprenza (phentermine)." Akrimax Pharmaceuticals, Cranford, NJ.', 1767369485);
